# Willy's Links project rules

- **Stack**: Static `index.html`, `favicon.svg`, `js/schedule.js` at repo root; GitHub Pages from `main` branch `/`. No build step unless explicitly added.
- **Scope**: This repo is the **links hub** (family, friends, clients, customers). Prefer minimal, readable HTML/CSS; avoid frameworks unless the user asks.
- **Design**: Black background, Matcha-inspired accent colors per row, three-font system (see `index.html` and `AGENTS.md`). Keep mobile and widescreen layouts in sync when editing.
- **Links**: Replace placeholder `href` values with real URLs; keep anchor text concise for mobile. Descriptions are desktop-only (hidden on narrow viewports).
- **Git**: Default branch `main`. Commit messages: short imperative subject, optional body for DNS/Pages/domain changes.
- **GitHub Pages**: Project site path under account may redirect to `sqazi.sh/links/`; custom domain **shahzeb.me** is configured on this repo in GitHub Settings → Pages (not in the user-site repo).
- **Secrets**: Never commit API keys, tokens, or private analytics IDs in plain HTML; use env-injected build steps only if a build is introduced later.
